<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="84" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[136,1452,266,1805]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis box="[136,321,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Evergreen shrub</emphasis>
, semi-prostate, 
<quantity box="[500,613,266,293]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" unit="m" value="1.0" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1.5 m</quantity>
tall. 
<emphasis box="[669,819,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Mature stems</emphasis>
brown or pale yellow, subterete, not verruculose. 
<emphasis box="[1378,1451,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Spines</emphasis>
3-fid, concolorous, 
<quantity box="[362,494,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" unit="cm" value="1.35" valueMax="2.2" valueMin="0.5">0.5–2.2 cm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[508,586,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Leaves</emphasis>
subsessile; leaf blade narrowly-elliptic to elliptic or sometimes lanceolate, abaxially green and usually strongly pruinose, adaxially dark green; 5.8–9.0 × 
<quantity box="[1036,1165,338,364]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" unit="cm" value="2.1" valueMax="2.9" valueMin="1.3">1.3–2.9 cm</quantity>
, thinly-leathery; midvein abaxially raised and adaxially impressed, lateral veins slightly raised, the secondary veins pinnate, jointly looped and muliti-festooned, the tertiary veins weakly reticulate if present; base cuneate, margins remotely spinose with spinules of 7–16 with 3.0–9.0 mm apart on each side, apex acuminate or mucronate. 
<emphasis box="[989,1139,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Inflorescence</emphasis>
a fascicle or rarely a highly reduced umbel, 4–8-flowered. 
<emphasis box="[480,553,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Bracts</emphasis>
1 or 2 if present, pale green or yellow with reddish-tinged narrowly-triangular 2 × 
<quantity box="[159,226,518,544]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[237,321,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Pedicel</emphasis>
pale green with partly red, 
<quantity box="[628,757,518,544]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" unit="cm" value="2.05" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="1.3">1.3–2.8 cm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[767,887,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Bracteoles</emphasis>
2 or 3, red, triangular, 1.5 × 
<quantity box="[1208,1276,518,544]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[1286,1378,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Flowers</emphasis>
bright yellow. 
<emphasis box="[227,300,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Sepals</emphasis>
in 3 whorls, bright yellow, outer and middle sepals usually outwardly revolute, outer sepals yellow usually with reddish-tinged ovate 3 × 
<quantity box="[565,633,590,616]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
, middle sepals yellow ovate 5 × 
<quantity box="[1005,1094,590,617]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
, inner sepals yellow obovate or elliptic 6.5 × 
<quantity box="[286,375,626,653]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[386,456,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Petals</emphasis>
elliptic, 4.5 × 
<quantity box="[619,687,626,652]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
, base clawed with a pair of ovoid nectaries close to each other, apex incised. 
<emphasis box="[230,323,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Stamens</emphasis>
pale yellow ca. 
<quantity box="[507,574,662,688]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
, anther connective of stamen distinct, apex truncate. 
<emphasis box="[1171,1230,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Pistil</emphasis>
<quantity box="[1237,1303,662,689]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long. 
<emphasis box="[1374,1452,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Ovules</emphasis>
6. 
<emphasis box="[164,246,699,724]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Berries</emphasis>
black or dark blue, ellipsoid ca. 7 × 
<quantity box="[657,745,698,725]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
, more or less pruinose, estylose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[136,1452,266,1805]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,475,733,759]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Distinguishing features:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hayata" authorityYear="1915" box="[483,730,734,760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Berberis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mingetsensis">
<emphasis box="[483,730,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Berberis mingetsensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. C. Yu &amp; K. F. Chung. A. Flowering" authorityYear="2014" box="[880,991,735,760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Berberis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ravenii">
<emphasis box="[880,991,735,760]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">B. ravenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differing from the latter by its remotely spinose margin of leaves.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[136,1452,266,1805]" box="[189,1055,806,832]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,323,806,832]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Phenology:</emphasis>
— 
<emphasis box="[351,468,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Flowering</emphasis>
March–April, December; 
<emphasis box="[765,858,807,832]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Fruiting</emphasis>
May, September.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="84" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="23.[136,1452,266,1805]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,477,841,867]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Distribution &amp; habitat:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hayata" authorityYear="1915" box="[505,756,842,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Berberis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mingetsensis">
<emphasis box="[505,756,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Berberis mingetsensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an understory shrub of the coniferous and broad-leaved mixed forest of 
<quantity box="[317,500,878,904]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" unit="m" value="2550.0" valueMax="2800.0" valueMin="2300.0">2300 to 2800 m</quantity>
. Most individuals are found from 
<collectingCountry box="[887,969,878,904]" name="Taiwan" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
Pleione Nature Reserve (TW Pleione NR) of Alishan (
<figureCitation box="[271,434,914,941]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[136,229,1905,1927]" captionTargetBox="[240,1343,223,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[225,1362,209,1880]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Distributions of Berberis sect. Wallichianae of Taiwan and Luzon. A. Major mountain ranges in Taiwan, with possible type localities of B. aristatoserrulata and B. brevisepala. NR: Nature Preserve. MWH: Major Wildlife Habitat. Mts: Mountain Range. B. Distributions of B. aristatoserrulata, B. hayatana, and B. pengii. C. Distributions of B. chingshuiensis, B. mingetsensis, and B. nantoensis. D. Distributions of B. kawakamii, B. ravenii, and B. schaaliae. E. Distributions of B. brevisepala and B. tarokoensis. F. Distribution of B. barandana in Luzon Island of the Philippines." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5146520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5146520/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Fig. 6A &amp; 6C</figureCitation>
), especially from along the Mienyueh Spur Line of Alishan Forest Rail System, with the exception of a small, disjunct population in 
<collectingRegion box="[628,801,950,976]" country="Taiwan" name="Nantou" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Nantou County</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[136,1452,266,1805]" box="[189,485,985,1012]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,485,985,1012]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Chinese name: 眠月小ª</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[136,1452,266,1805]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,640,1021,1048]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Proposed IUCN conservation status:</emphasis>
—Critically Endangered [CR B1a+c(ii, iii)]. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hayata" authorityYear="1915" box="[1169,1420,1022,1048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Berberis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mingetsensis">
<emphasis box="[1169,1420,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Berberis mingetsensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from two restricted localities in 
<collectingRegion box="[640,943,1058,1084]" isEnumeration="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Chiayi and Nantou County</collectingRegion>
where they occur as scattered individuals on the mountain ridges or along the abandoned railway. Habitat disturbance brought about by tourists and development of the railway construction in Alishan areas may have a negative impact on the survival of the species (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[1259,1398,1130,1156]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" refId="ref24146" refString="IUCN (2012) IUCN red list category and criteria. Version 3.1. Second Edition. Gland and Cambridge, 32 pp." type="book" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[136,1452,266,1805]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1166,1192]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Notes:</emphasis>
This rare species has an early and complicated taxonomic history (
<tableCitation box="[1008,1095,1166,1192]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="2.[145,236,544,568]" captionText="TABLE 2. Taxonomic history of Berberis sect. Wallichianae of Taiwan. Species in bold denote the author(s) and year of publication." pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Table 2</tableCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Mizushima, M." box="[1114,1321,1166,1193]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" pagination="28 - 32" refId="ref25407" refString="Mizushima, M. (1954) Questions to Formosan barberries (I). Contributions from the Research Institute for Natural Resources 35: 28 - 32." type="journal article" year="1954">Mizushima (1954)</bibRefCitation>
argued that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hayata" authorityYear="1915" box="[136,382,1202,1228]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Berberis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mingetsensis">
<emphasis box="[136,382,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Berberis mingetsensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to the Chinese species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leveille" authorityYear="1911" box="[808,920,1202,1228]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Berberis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[808,920,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">B. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, though he refrained from uniting the two. This was clearly a mistaken since 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leveille" authorityYear="1911" box="[469,582,1238,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Berberis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[469,582,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">B. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unique in being the only species in the whole genus with flowers that are white and red whereas the flowers of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hayata" authorityYear="1915" box="[568,743,1275,1300]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Berberis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mingetsensis">
<emphasis box="[568,743,1275,1300]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">B. mingetsensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are yellow. Unfortunately, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mizushima, M." box="[1056,1283,1274,1301]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" pagination="28 - 32" refId="ref25407" refString="Mizushima, M. (1954) Questions to Formosan barberries (I). Contributions from the Research Institute for Natural Resources 35: 28 - 32." type="journal article" year="1954">Mizushima’s (1954)</bibRefCitation>
statement was taken into action by 
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, T. - S." box="[361,474,1310,1336]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" refId="ref24796" refString="Liu, T. - S. (1960) Illustrations of Native and Introduced Ligneous Plants of Taiwan, vol. 1. College of Agriculture, National Taiwan University, Taipei, 702 pp." type="book" year="1960">Liu (1960</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, T. - S." box="[484,544,1310,1337]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" pagination="515 - 521" refId="ref24833" refString="Liu, T. - S. (1976) Berberidaceae. In: Li, H. - L., Liu, T. - S., Huang, T. - C., Koyama, T. &amp; DeVol, C. E. (Eds.) Flora of Taiwan, vol. 2. Epoch Publishing Co., Taipei, pp. 515 - 521." type="book chapter" year="1976">1976</bibRefCitation>
), whose treatment also followed in 
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, T. - S. &amp; Liao, J. - C." box="[937,1142,1310,1336]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" refId="ref24907" refString="Liu, T. - S. &amp; Liao, J. - C. (1980) Dendrology. The Commercial Press, Ltd., Taipei, 1252 pp." type="book" year="1980">Liu &amp; Liao (1980)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, Y. - C. &amp; Lu, F. - Y. &amp; Ou, C. - H." box="[1194,1368,1310,1336]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" refId="ref24939" refString="Liu, Y. - C., Lu, F. - Y. &amp; Ou, C. - H. (1988) Trees of Taiwan. College of Agriculture, National Chung-Shing University, Taichung, 1019 pp." type="book" year="1988">
Liu 
<emphasis box="[1239,1295,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">et al.</emphasis>
(1988
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, Y. - C. &amp; Lu, F. - Y. &amp; Ou, C. - H." box="[1379,1439,1310,1336]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" refId="ref24982" refString="Liu, Y. - C., Lu, F. - Y. &amp; Ou, C. - H. (1994) Trees of Taiwan, Revised edition. College of Agriculture, National Chung-Shing University, Taichung, 925 pp." type="book" year="1994">1994</bibRefCitation>
). Subsequently 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hayata" authorityYear="1915" box="[293,467,1347,1372]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Berberis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mingetsensis">
<emphasis box="[293,467,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">B. mingetsensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was synonymized under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hayata" authorityYear="1913" box="[749,969,1346,1372]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Berberis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aristatoserrulata">
<emphasis box="[749,969,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">B. aristatoserrulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without explanation by Chamberlain &amp; Hu (1984) and this was followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ying, T." box="[504,634,1382,1408]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" pagination="50 - 306" refId="ref26828" refString="Ying, T. (2001) Berberidaceae. In: Ying, T. (Ed.) Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae, Tomus 29. Sceince Press, Beijing, pp. 50 - 306." type="book chapter" year="2001">Ying (2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ying, J." box="[645,705,1382,1408]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" pagination="715 - 771" refId="ref26752" refString="Ying, J. (2011) Berberis L. In: Wu, Z. - Y., Raven, P. H. &amp; Hong, D. - Y. (Eds.) Flora of China, vol. 19 (Cucurbitaceae through Valerianaceae, with Annonaceae and Berberidaceae. Science Press &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden, Beijing &amp; St. Louis, Missouri, pp. 715 - 771." type="book chapter" year="2011">2011</bibRefCitation>
). In 1963, Li corrected the species epithet to ‘ 
<emphasis box="[1219,1376,1383,1408]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">mingetsuensis</emphasis>
’, as to make it conform to the spelling of its 
<typeStatus box="[549,597,1418,1444]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">type</typeStatus>
locality ‘Mingetsukei’ (which literally means Mingetsu ‘creek’) and this was followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lu, S. - Y. &amp; Yang, Y. - P." box="[275,479,1454,1481]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" pagination="575 - 585" refId="ref25096" refString="Lu, S. - Y. &amp; Yang, Y. - P. (1996) Berberidaceae. In: Editorial Committee of the Flora of Taiwan (Eds.) Flora of Taiwan, vol. 2, Second Edition. Department of Botany, National Taiwan University, Taipei, pp. 575 - 585." type="book chapter" year="1996">Lu &amp; Yang (1996)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, Y. - P. &amp; Liu, H. - Y. &amp; Lu, S. - Y." box="[489,690,1454,1480]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" refId="ref26694" refString="Yang, Y. - P., Liu, H. - Y. &amp; Lu, S. - Y. (eds.) (1997) Manual of Taiwan Vascular Plants, vol. 2. II. Spermatophyta. The Council of Agriculture, The Executive Yuan, Taipei, 352 pp." type="book" year="1997">
Yang 
<emphasis box="[552,608,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">et al.</emphasis>
(1997)
</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Lu, F. - Y. &amp; Ou, C. - H. &amp; Chen, Y. - C. &amp; Chi, Y. - S. &amp; Lu, K. - C. &amp; Tseng, Y. - H." box="[747,922,1454,1480]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" refId="ref25028" refString="Lu, F. - Y., Ou, C. - H., Chen, Y. - C., Chi, Y. - S., Lu, K. - C. &amp; Tseng, Y. - H. (2010) Trees of Taiwan, vol. 3. Published by Chern-Hsiung Ou, Taichung, 615 pp." type="book" year="2010">
Lu 
<emphasis box="[784,839,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
. However there is no reason to believe Hayata’s use of ‘mingetsensis’ was not intentional since he also applied it to his 
<taxonomicName authority="Hayata (1915: 40 - 42)" authorityName="Hayata" authorityPageNumber="40 - 42" authorityYear="1915" box="[967,1452,1490,1517]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mingetsensis">
<emphasis box="[967,1190,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Rubus mingetsensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hayata, B." box="[1200,1452,1490,1517]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" refId="ref23908" refString="Hayata, B. (1915) Icones Plantarum Formosanarum, vol. 5. Bureau of Productive Industries, Government of Formosa, Taihoku, 358 pp." type="book" year="1915">Hayata (1915: 40–42)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
whose 
<typeStatus box="[216,264,1526,1552]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">type</typeStatus>
was also collected in Mingetsukei. One possible explanation for his leaving out the letter ‘u’ from these two names is because there is no difference between the Japanese pronunciation of ‘mingetsuensis’ and ‘mingetsensis.’ Given this in accordance with Art. 60.1 of the Melbourne Code (
<bibRefCitation author="McNeill, J. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Buck, W. R. &amp; Demoulin, V. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Prud'homme van Reine, W. F. &amp; Smith, G. F. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Turland, N. J." box="[858,1081,1598,1624]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" refId="ref25242" refString="McNeill, J., Barrie, F. R., Buck, W. R., Demoulin, V., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Marhold, K., Prado, J., Prud'homme van Reine, W. F., Smith, G. F., Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Turland, N. J. (Eds.) (2012) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi and plants (Melbourne Code) adopted by the Eighteenth International Botanical Congress Melbourne, Australia, July 2011. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein, 240 pp. [Regnum Vegetabile 154]" type="book" year="2012">
McNeill 
<emphasis box="[960,1017,1598,1624]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
) Hayata’s name stands.
</paragraph>
